From 79e7901a6e7f2ec72128ef4785edf7d835666e64 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Feb 2026 11:36:44 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Move language selection to settings modal and make item
 detection locale-aware
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

### Motivation

- Centralize user-facing text into a stable i18n surface and avoid Fast Refresh / export-of-non-components issues by providing a runtime/provider separation.
- Make parsing and item-category/icon detection locale-aware so the app recognizes item names in the active language (e.g. `apfel` in `de`, `apple` in `en`, `manzana` in `es`).

### Description

- Added an i18n runtime and React integration under `apps/web/src/i18n/` including `config.ts`, `runtime.ts`, `I18nProvider.tsx`, `context.ts`, `useI18n.ts`, `resources.ts`, and locale resolution tests (`resolveLocale.test.ts`, `resources.test.ts`).
- Wired i18n into app bootstrap by calling `initializeLocale()` and wrapping `<App />` with `<I18nProvider />` in `main.tsx`.
- Moved the language picker out of the drawer list area and implemented a settings popup opened from the existing settings button at the bottom of the sidebar; the modal contains the language selector and a close action (changes in `ListsDrawer.tsx`).
- Made UI text locale-aware by replacing hardcoded strings with `t(...)` and `useI18n()` in components (`App.tsx`, `AddItemDialog.tsx`, `AppHeader.tsx`, `BottomBar.tsx`, `CreateListModal.tsx`, `EditItemModal.tsx`, etc.).
- Implemented locale-scoped item-name detection and icon resolution in `apps/web/src/domain/categories.ts` via a `localizedItemEntries` map and updated `getCategoryForItem`, `getCategoryOrder`, and `getItemIcon` to accept a `locale` (defaulting to the resolved locale).
- Made the input parser locale-aware by adding `parseAmount(input, locale)` and `parseItemInput(input, locale)` with EN/ES unit aliases while preserving existing DE behavior (changes in `inputParser.ts`).
- Updated and added unit tests for the new behavior (`domain/categories.test.ts`, `domain/inputParser.test.ts`, `i18n/*` tests) to cover locale-specific detection and key parity.

### Testing

- Ran lint: `npm run lint -w apps/web` — passed.
- Ran typecheck: `npm run typecheck -w apps/web` — passed.
- Ran unit tests: `npm run test -w apps/web` — Vitest suite passed (unit tests passed; Playwright E2E file initially skipped then executed).
- Ran Playwright E2E with browser install: `npx playwright install chromium`, `npx playwright install-deps chromium`, and `RUN_PLAYWRIGHT_E2E=1 npm run test -w apps/web -- src/e2e.backend-frontend.playwright.test.ts` — passed.
- Ran production build: `npm run build -w apps/web` — passed.
